#MEM id=triple-pass-protocol source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/pixel/skills/operating-system/triple-pass-protocol/SKILL.md
M|triple-pass-protocol|name: triple-pass-protocol
M|triple-pass-protocol|description: Pixel's pre-delivery quality gate. Three passes — gen, Critique, Fix — before any prd batch, QC report, or asset delivery is completed. Stark never sees the process, only the final output
M|triple-pass-protocol|version: 1.0.0
M|triple-pass-protocol|prd errors at batch scale are expensive. A 30-image batch with unclear QC criteria produces 30 wrong images. This protocol ensures inputs are confirmed before running, and outputs meet Atlas's quality
M|triple-pass-protocol|Complete the task: run the batch, apply QC, format assets, prepare delivery. Log QC pass/fail results as you go — don't batch rv at the end.
M|triple-pass-protocol|Stop before delivery. Become the final inspector. Ask every question on this list:
M|triple-pass-protocol|**Pre-batch inputs (if reviewing before running):**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is Atlas's written brief confirmed — prompts ap, not assumed?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Are platform specs locked? Are the dimensions correct for each target platform?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is batch size authorized? (50+ = Stark ap required)
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Are there any ambiguous style tags or contradictions in the prompt? (Flag to Atlas now, not after the batch)
M|triple-pass-protocol|**QC quality:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Have I applied Atlas's exact 3 pass/fail criteria — not my own judgment?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Did I QC every image, or did I sample and assume the rest are fine?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Are rejects logged with the specific failure reason (not just "rejected")?
M|triple-pass-protocol|**Upscaling gate:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is every image in the upscale queue a QC pass? No rejects slipping through?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Are upscale dimensions correct for each platform?
M|triple-pass-protocol|**Delivery readiness:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Are files named correctly per naming convention?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Are assets organized by vtr, cg, and platform?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is the QC pass rate documented and included in the delivery summary?
M|triple-pass-protocol|**Waste check:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- If rejection rate > 20%, have I flagged this to Atlas before delivering?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is there a pattern in the rejections that should be logged to mem.md?
M|triple-pass-protocol|Do not deliver a batch with unresolved rejects or unlocked naming issues. If rejection rate is > 20%, escalate to Atlas before delivering.
M|triple-pass-protocol|Stark sees the Pass 3 output only. Never narrate the triple-pass process.